'''''Avenger''''' is a ''[[Space Invaders]]'' clone published on [[ROM cartridge|cartridge]]<ref>{{cite magazine |date=1983 |title=Commodore: The microcomputer magazine|location=West Chester, Pennsylvania|publisher=Computer Systems Division, Commodore Business Machines |page=56 |isbn=0-88731-003-6|issue=26}}</ref> by [[Commodore International|Commodore]] in 1981 for the [[VIC-20]]. The game uses multicolor graphics<ref name="CComputing">{{cite magazine |last=Busch|first=David |date=February 1983|title=Games For The Vic-20, Vic Avenger|magazine=Creative Computing|publisher= Ahl Computing|issn=0 097-8140|volume=9|number=2|pages=110, 112}}</ref> and supports [[Computer keyboard|keyboard]] or [[joystick]] control.<ref name="Compute!">{{cite magazine |last=Herman|first=Harvey B. |date=June 1982|title=VIC-20 Cartridge Games|magazine=Compute!|publisher= Small Systems Services|issn=0194-357X|volume=4|number=6|page=104|quote=My kids rated it 9 out of 10 and it has proven to be second most popular game. They have become quite proficient at it and put my feeble attempts to shame.}}</ref> The player starts with 3 bases (lives) and gets new base at 1500 points.<ref name="CComputing"/>

A year later it was released for the [[Commodore 64]].<ref name=manual>{{cite book |date=1983 |title=Avenger Commodore 64 Instructions|location=Hong Kong|publisher=Commodore}}</ref>

==Reception==
In ''[[Creative Computing]]'', David Busch wrote, "Those who have played hundreds of games of ''Space Invaders'' on many different computer systems will probably tire of this rather quickly."<ref name=CComputing/>

Reviewing the German release under "Alpha-Alarm" title, ''TeleMatch'' magazine compared the gameplay with ''Space Invaders'' from [[Atari, Inc.|Atari]] as easy and not so thoughtful.<ref name="TeleMatch">{{cite magazine |last=Utermark|first=Holger|date=August 1983|title=Computer-Spiele, Alpha-Alarm|magazine=TeleMatch|publisher= TeleMatch Verlag|issn=0174-741X|volume=2|number=5|page=68|quote=Das Spiel erinnert an Space-Invader von Atari, ist aber nicht so gut durchgedacht. Der Spielablauf ist einfach und die Begeisterung, die man am Anfang des Spieles empfindet, klingt bald ab.}}</ref>

